-- Relocation services provider Sirva files for IPO of up to $175 mln
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 11:53AM EDT
-- None



March 28 (Reuters) - Sirva Inc [SIRVA.UL], which provides relocation services, filed with U.S. regulators on Friday to raise up to $175 million in an initial public offering of common stock.

The Oakbrook Terrace, Illinois-based company told the U.S Securities and Exchange Commission in a preliminary prospectus that Morgan Stanley, Goldman Sachs & Co and J.P. Morgan were the lead underwriters for the offering. The filing did not reveal how many shares the company planned to sell or their expected price. (http://r.reuters.com/zup97v) The company did not specify the exchange it intends to list its common stock on or the symbol.